description:
Portugal strengthened the National Health Service (SNS) by:  
"Exceptional human resources regime, which includes:
(i) suspension of overtime limits; 
(ii) simplifying the hiring of workers;
(iii) worker mobility;
(iv) hiring retired doctors without being subject to age limits.
Prevention regime for professionals in the health sector directly involved in the diagnosis and specialized laboratory response.
Exceptional regime for the purchase of services by organs, agencies, services and entities of the Ministry of Health.
Exceptional regime for the composition of medical boards for assessing the disabilities of people with disabilities."March 12

[Portugal, Restriction and Regulation of Government Services measures 2020]. Presidency of the Council of Ministers set exceptional and temporary measures to respond to the pandemic of the disease COVID -19, designed to allow the practice of acts by means of remote communication under:
a) Urgent processes that run under the terms of the Justices of the Peace;
b) Procedures and acts of registration;
c) Procedures conducted by the National Institute of Industrial Property, IP
